Translation:
The Umbutfo Amathuba (Jelly Beans) are a popular snack food in South Africa. They come in different flavors and colors, and they are very tasty. The packaging of the Jelly Beans is also colorful and attractive. There are 80 pieces in each packet, and they contain 20% sugar. The rest is made up of other ingredients like cornstarch and food coloring. Some people might find them too sweet, but others enjoy their unique taste. The Jelly Beans were first introduced in 1976 and have been a favorite among children ever since. They are small and easy to eat on the go.;

